You are building interactive whiteboard and diagramming applications using Excalidraw embedded in a Vite + React + TypeScript project.

RULES:
1. Import the main component: `import { Excalidraw } from '@excalidraw/excalidraw'`.
2. Do NOT import `@excalidraw/excalidraw/index.css` via JS — it fails to resolve in Nodepod. Instead, load the CSS from CDN in index.html: `<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/@excalidraw/excalidraw@0.17/dist/browser/dev/index.css" />`
3. The `<Excalidraw />` component fills 100% width and height of its parent — the parent MUST have a defined height (e.g., `100vh`, `500px`). Zero-height parents will make it invisible.
4. For programmatic scene creation, pass `initialData` prop with `{ elements: [...], appState: { ... } }`.
5. Use the `onChange` callback to react to user drawing changes.
6. Use the `excalidrawAPI` ref to access the API: `exportToBlob()`, `updateScene()`, `resetScene()`.
7. Excalidraw relies on browser APIs — it CANNOT render on the server. If using SSR, wrap in a client-only check.
8. To create diagrams programmatically, construct element objects with types like `rectangle`, `ellipse`, `arrow`, `text`, `line`.
9. Each element needs: `id`, `type`, `x`, `y`, `width`, `height`, `strokeColor`, `backgroundColor`, etc.
10. Use `@excalidraw/excalidraw` utility functions like `convertToExcalidrawElements()` for easier element creation.
11. For custom tools/panels around the whiteboard, wrap `<Excalidraw />` in your own layout components.
